{#
  src/teller/domains/treasury/prompt.j2 — Treasury-domain overlay.

  Extends prompts/base.j2 and fills domain-specific blocks with the
  Treasury Bulletin content carved from the Arena-winning prompt
  (arena-cohort0/prompts/goose_prompt.j2 lines 14-25, 49-54 example,
  57-64, 66-69, 76-79).

  The combined rendered output is the prompt fed to the model for
  treasury-domain questions. Semantic equivalence to the Arena-winning
  prompt is validated by the 20-question regression (ADR-004/ADR-005),
  not by byte-string equality.

  Changes to the iron rules are forbidden — they live in the base and
  are locked by ADR-001.
#}
{% extends "base.j2" %}

{% block workflow_multi_period -%}
For multi-year questions: search LATEST year FIRST for a retrospective summary table. One table beats 12 files. Example: "1969-1980" → grep 1981/1982 bulletins first.
{%- endblock %}

{% block domain_unit_conversion -%}
UNIT CONVERSION (the #1 error pattern):
- Table says "thousands" + question says "nominal dollars" → MULTIPLY by 1,000
- Table says "millions" + question says "nominal dollars" → MULTIPLY by 1,000,000
- Table says "millions" + question says "in millions" → no conversion
- Table says "thousands" + question says "in millions" → DIVIDE by 1,000
- Parenthetical (234) = NEGATIVE. "n.a." = not available, NOT zero.
- Check FOUR places for unit: table title, header row, column header, footnotes.
{%- endblock %}

{% block domain_time_conventions -%}
FISCAL YEAR:
- Before 1976: FY = Jul 1 – Jun 30. FY1975 = Jul 1974 – Jun 1975
- After 1976: FY = Oct 1 – Sep 30. FY2024 = Oct 2023 – Sep 2024
- "Calendar year" ≠ "fiscal year" — different months.
{%- endblock %}

{% block domain_table_example %}  | | Public Debt - Interest-bearing - Marketable | Public Debt - Interest-bearing - Non-marketable | Public Debt - Total |
Value "1,234" under "Marketable" means "Marketable Interest-bearing Public Debt = $1,234" — NOT total Public Debt.{% endblock %}

{% block domain_traps -%}
DOMAIN TRAPS:
- "reported IN Feb 1938" → MUST open treasury_bulletin_1938_02.txt. Never substitute another bulletin.
- "Capital"/"Paid-in capital" = original appropriation ($200M). "Total capital"/"Fund balance" = capital + earnings ($8B). Use TOTAL unless question says "paid-in".
- "Net receipts" = total minus refunds. "Net outlays" = outlays minus offsetting receipts.
- "Gross debt" includes intragovernmental. "Debt held by public" excludes them.
- "Interest on public debt" ≠ "interest credited to government accounts".
- "Receipts" (revenue) ≠ Treasury receipt instruments (securities). "Expenditures" ≠ "Outlays" (may differ in scope).
- Later bulletins may revise figures. If question doesn't say "reported in", check next 1-2 bulletins.
{%- endblock %}

{% block domain_multi_file -%}
MULTI-FILE QUESTIONS:
- Search LATEST year first for retrospective table: grep -n "metric" /app/corpus/treasury_bulletin_1981_*.txt
- Batch grep: grep -h "metric" /app/corpus/treasury_bulletin_196*.txt /app/corpus/treasury_bulletin_197*.txt
- Track in dict: needed=list(range(1969,1981)); found={}; verify len(found)==len(needed) before computing.
{%- endblock %}

{% block domain_external_data -%}
EXTERNAL DATA (not in bulletins):
CPI-U annual (BLS, 1982-84=100): 1938:14.1, 1940:14.0, 1945:18.0, 1950:24.1, 1955:26.8, 1960:29.6, 1965:31.5, 1970:38.8, 1975:53.8, 1979:72.6, 1980:82.4, 1985:107.6, 1990:130.7, 1995:152.4, 2000:172.2, 2005:195.3, 2010:218.1, 2015:237.0, 2020:258.8
Real dollars: nominal*(CPI_target/CPI_source)
Historical dates: WWII ended 1945. Korean War began June 1950. Vietnam 1955-1975.
{%- endblock %}
